# Keep the Docker build context lean. The Dockerfile `COPY . .` ships the whole workspace (it needs
# gui/scripts/lib + packages/*/src to build), so prune everything the build re-creates or never uses.
#
# NOTE: paths are relative to the BUILD CONTEXT root. Run the build with the repo root as context and
# this file as -f deploy/control-vm/Dockerfile … (or copy this .dockerignore to the repo root as
# .dockerignore for the build — see README.md).

# VCS + editor
.git
.gitignore
**/.DS_Store

# All node_modules (pnpm reinstalls in the build stage from the lockfile)
node_modules
**/node_modules

# Build outputs (the build stage regenerates dist + gui/dist)
**/dist
**/build
gui/dist
**/*.tsbuildinfo

# Worktrees + other deploy trees (the e2b/daytona images, this dir's own git noise)
.claude/worktrees
deploy/e2b/node_modules
deploy/daytona/node_modules

# Test/coverage/log noise
**/coverage
**/.vitest
**/*.log
npm-debug.log*

# Local env / secrets — NEVER ship these into an image
.env
.env.*
**/.env
**/.env.*
**/.credentials.json

# Runs + collected data (never bake a product's data; see CLAUDE.md data boundaries)
**/.pi
**/.piflow/*/runs
